      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "That perspective highlights the classic debate between futile suffering and peaceful acceptance, a theme central to many literary and philosophical works. Choosing a canonical moment of release isn't a failure of the narrative, but rather a powerful assertion of free will and dignity in the face of inevitability. It is often more compelling to write a character who finds the strength to let go of a broken existence on their own terms, as this final act of control can resonate deeply with your readers.",
